<subSubSection id="31AD0F895960581558C3C3CFF863542C" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" type="description">
<paragraph id="79085C025960581558C3C3CFF84B5568" blockId="3.[174,1233,996,1045]" box="[174,355,1023,1045]" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">S. Amini (ZMUT).</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79085C0259605815588EC407F8A255AC" blockId="3.[174,1233,1078,1361]" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">
It has been shown so far from Europe, from 
<collectingCountry id="01A01C92596058155A8DC407FA18552C" box="[736,816,1079,1105]" name="France" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">France</collectingCountry>
to the central areas of the European part of 
<collectingCountry id="01A01C92596058155965C466F87F550D" box="[264,343,1110,1136]" name="Russia" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">Russia</collectingCountry>
, to the north reaching Scandinavia and south to 
<collectingCountry id="01A01C92596058155BC5C466FAC8550D" box="[936,992,1110,1136]" name="Italy" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">Italy</collectingCountry>
. As host fungi were most often shown: 
<taxonomicName id="BEB727815960581559F9C446FA7A55EC" authority="(Willd.) P. Karst." authorityName="P. Karst." baseAuthorityName="Willd." box="[404,850,1142,1169]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Meruliaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="adusta">
<emphasis id="4BC380105960581559F9C446FB5255ED" box="[404,634,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">Bjerkandera adusta</emphasis>
(Willd.) P. Karst.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="BEB72781596058155B32C447FD1655ED" box="[863,1086,1142,1168]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Fomes" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fomentarius">
<emphasis id="4BC38010596058155B32C447FD1655ED" box="[863,1086,1142,1168]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">Fomes fomentarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Fr. and 
<taxonomicName id="BEB727815960581558C3C4A7FA3755CD" authority="(Bull.) P. Karst. (Reibnitz, 1999)" authorityName="P. Karst. (Reibnitz" authorityYear="1999" baseAuthorityName="Bull." box="[174,799,1174,1201]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Fomitopsidaceae" genus="Piptoporus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Polyporales" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="betulinus">
<emphasis id="4BC380105960581558C3C4A7F8B555CD" box="[174,413,1174,1200]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">Piptoporus betulinus</emphasis>
(Bull.) P. Karst. (
<bibRefCitation id="1D2621F3596058155A05C4A6FA3F55CD" author="Reibnitz, J." box="[616,791,1174,1200]" pageId="3" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 76" refId="ref7989" refString="Reibnitz, J. 1999. Verbreitung und Lebensraume der Baumschwammfresser Sudwestdeutschlands (Coleoptera: Cisidae). Mitteilungen Entomologischer Verein Stuttgart, 34, 1 - 76." type="journal article" year="1999">Reibnitz, 1999</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. It is also found under the loose bark of deciduous trees.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="79085C0259605815588EC4E6F863542C" blockId="3.[174,1233,1078,1361]" pageId="3" pageNumber="320">
